bnf

Enum TokenType

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<TokenType>
      • bnf.TokenType
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<TokenType>

    public enum TokenType
extends java.lang.Enum<TokenType>
    An enum of types to be used with the Token class as the types of those tokens. The types enumerated here are useful in the processing of BNF notation, denoting the various parts of BNF notation and ways of processing BNF notation.
    Version:
    CIT594 Spring 2013
    Author:
    Michael McLaughlin, mvm@cis.upenn.edu
